58. Nisi te nala re magna nacturi cupis] The verb macto deserves particular notice. It seems to be derived from the same root as inagis and magnus, and to be a frequentative form of an obsolete verb, mago, of which the participle nactus remained in use. 1. The original signification of macto was ‘to magnify,' ‘to glorify,' in the sense of paying homage to a deity by offerings or sacrifices, and thence was applied to men when 'exalted by honour. In this sense it is constructed with the accusative of the object to which homage is pald, and the ablative ol the object employed to testify homage.
